		<pb n="1"/>
			<p><hi rend="underline">32 F</hi></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Palmyra</placeName>&#44; <date>Sept. 18<hi rend="sup">th</hi>&#44; 1851</date>.</p>
			<p>Dear friend&#58;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I have written this article more than a month<lb/> ago for you. An eye infection however prevented me to finish<lb/> it sooner and copy it for you. At the moment I am vacationing<lb/> and hasten to send it to you. I do not doubt that you will have<lb/> to correct it. Very much so indeed. &#40;But I am sure that this<lb/> article will then be not unworthy of your journal and may be a<lb/> seed grain for many a good decision.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I presume that you have received by now the bible<lb/> and one sheet of <persName>Reggio&#39;s</persName> DENKBUCHLEIN. You would make me happy<lb/> and honor him who deserves honor if you would print in one of<lb/> your journals a literary biographic note concerning this great<lb/> old man&#44; with ever young spirit. I also sent you two journals<lb/> &#40;I don&#39;t have any more. I believe many more are in existence.&#41;<lb/> of a talmudic dictionary. I don&#39;t have any use for it. Maybe<lb/> you care to have this work sent to you from <placeName>Europe</placeName>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Sometime ago I asked you to design statutes &#40;STATUTEN<lb/> ENTWURF&#41;. The congregation for which I did that is a small one and<lb/> poor one with a <sic>Bohemean</sic> rite &#40;similar to the small Polish rite&#41;.<lb/> This congregation now made some statutes for itself&#44; will try them<lb/> out for a while and after they have experience will draw them up<lb/> anew with the aid of sample statutes and shape them properly.<lb/> &#40;28 members&#44; &#36;7.50 for seats for men and wife&#59; 5. for single<lb/> persons&#59; 10&#162; weekly contribution.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Well&#44; good&#45;bye dear friend&#44; and allow the old wish&#44;<lb/> &#42;KETIBA wa&#45;ha&#45;ti&#45;ma tobah.</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Most cordially yours&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">ISIDOR BUSH</persName></p>
			<p>&#42;<sic>Iscribed</sic> for good life.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Addressed&#58; <addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee>&#44; Editor Occident&#44; etc. <placeName>Philada</placeName>.</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Palmyra</placeName> <date>Sept. 18&#44; 1851</date>.</p>
			<p>Translation in General files.</p>
			<p>Letter speaks of a manuscript sent <persName>Leeser</persName>&#44; for publication<lb/> It also speaks of having sent <sic>abible</sic> and one sheet of <persName>Reggio&#39;s</persName><lb/> Denkbuchlein. Mentions other books which <persName>Leeser</persName> may want.</p>
        
